er via `withHandler`, or poll for the value via\nthe new `poll` method.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D7896", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/build.gradle", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/androidTest/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/test/GeckoResultTest.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoResult.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "740c3623a44aed64203d830a03682e14f90917f9", "parents": ["50cc3c94b20d7ba104fc24b887e15064cad69d41"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1493796 - [mozprocess] Revert poll() behavior on Windows due to regression. r=gbrown\n\nOriginally landed as changeset 8793e332890e via bug 1433905 the\npatch caused a regression because GetExitCodeProcess() returns\n0 for an inside of Firefox restarted process.\n\nIt can be relanded once the process id of the job object can\nsuccessfully be tracked.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9020", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_quit_restart.py", "testing/mozbase/mozprocess/mozprocess/processhandler.py", "testing/mozbase/mozprocess/tests/test_poll.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9782e0b1657da7b2742e693222f8ac912920b521", "parents": ["740c3623a44aed64203d830a03682e14f90917f9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1499057: webdriver: fix element comparison assertions; r=whimboo\n\nThe Python \"is\" operator tests object identity, but the tests should\nrely on the webdriver.Element equality implementation, __eq__.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9127", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/webdriver/tests/element_send_keys/interactability.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b5b389d5788ed89f7e666c4de6e80e6a3cb99a19", "parents": ["9782e0b1657da7b2742e693222f8ac912920b521"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1499057: webdriver: remove known web element cache; r=whimboo\n\nThe known web element cache in the WebDriver test client, or\nwebdriver.Session._element_cache, is used only to avoid constructing\nnew webdriver.Element instances of the same web element and serves\nno practical purpose beyond that\n\nSince this client is intended for testing purposes, we would like\nto be able to construct duplicate webdriver.Element instances,\nso that e.g. fake elements can be constructed and send to the remote end.\n\nDepends on D9127\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8855", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/webdriver/webdriver/client.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "55724db90e3e23b09e946681067567c489023249", "parents": ["b5b389d5788ed89f7e666c4de6e80e6a3cb99a19"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1494229 - [marionette] Improve documentation for new contributors. r=ato\n\nDONTBUILD\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8981", "files": ["testing/marionette/doc/Building.md", "testing/marionette/doc/NewContributors.md", "testing/marionette/doc/Testing.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "17432131026dfd5e16a8a2935fa4421c56be585e", "parents": ["55724db90e3e23b09e946681067567c489023249"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1494229 - [marionette] Advertise Phabricator for submitting patches in the docs. r=ato\n\nDONTBUILD\n\nDepends on D8981\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8982", "files": ["testing/marionette/doc/Patches.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "228e7fe1545959bf5cedfe6e25c5e8dd91ec0a1a", "parents": ["17432131026dfd5e16a8a2935fa4421c56be585e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499504 - Always include search icon in search boxes on Mac r=dao\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9021", "files": ["toolkit/themes/osx/global/in-content/common.css", "toolkit/themes/shared/extensions/extensions.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a404545425a2d59f36f3acadc99f1a55c366429", "parents": ["228e7fe1545959bf5cedfe6e25c5e8dd91ec0a1a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499944 - Don't show detail view when changing plugin state r=jaws\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9061", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b0a8e47d25608312af369290db040fa9009ddcf", "parents": ["9a404545425a2d59f36f3acadc99f1a55c366429"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1495706 - Move add-on version to list at bottom from heading r=jaws\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9058", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "272fbc5589a88513c9e9212d94bc6792731bc434", "parents": ["7b0a8e47d25608312af369290db040fa9009ddcf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499109 - Wrap extension name in about:addons r=jaws\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9012", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.css", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/content/extensions.xml", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_bug580298.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_list.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/browser_updateid.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "54315f38f9050ca56c2ff9e7825838791ae45cca", "parents": ["272fbc5589a88513c9e9212d94bc6792731bc434"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Wes Kocher \u003cwkocher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499866 - Update wpt metadata for idlharness.window.js on fennec r=jgraham\n\nFennec supports orientation attributes and properties, so these were unexpectedly passing.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9028", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/compat/idlharness.window.js.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9db2b627026f6e936b4ab8529479e3a84ad51a39", "parents": ["54315f38f9050ca56c2ff9e7825838791ae45cca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Parks \u003cdparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426733: Use restricting SIDs in Windows NPAPI process sandbox (r=bobowen)\n\nAllow NPAPI sandbox to use restricting SIDs.  This hardens the plugin sandbox.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8746", "files": ["security/sandbox/win/src/sandboxbroker/sandboxBroker.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b976167b45aa1ea14c163e0dd4480ec1439289b", "parents": ["9db2b627026f6e936b4ab8529479e3a84ad51a39"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris Martin \u003ccmartin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1496364 - Minor refactor to stop uninitialized variable warning r=handyman\n\nThe compiler warns that jobLevel is uninitialized if none of the if-else\nconditions are true. Simply replacing the leading assert with a\n\"else crash\" tells the compiler that case will never actually happen.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8841", "files": ["security/sandbox/win/src/sandboxbroker/sandboxBroker.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5441249fe31416707df434bc6f886d923543de46", "parents": ["9b976167b45aa1ea14c163e0dd4480ec1439289b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mathieu Leplatre \u003cmathieu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486980 - Fetch tippytop collection in one bulk with getAll() r=asuth,nanj\n\nIterating an IDB cursor generates a lot of overhead. In this patch, we upgrade the kinto-offline to its latest version that uses `getAll()` when no filter is specified. We leverage this change in tippytop, by omitting the filter and filtering the whole list there instead. This allowed us to go from ~1sec on a 1000 entries to ~70ms.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9076", "files": ["services/common/kinto-offline-client.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a05c09af3770321c9d3acd89204ac62f3fb1878", "parents": ["5441249fe31416707df434bc6f886d923543de46"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dana Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1498686 - avoid acquiring TransportSecurityInfo::mMutex in hot code r=jesup,jcj\n\nBefore this patch, Necko functions polling the state of TLS sockets\n(essentially, TransportSecurityInfo) would cause a considerable amount of\nlocking on TransportSecurityInfo::mMutex instances via GetErrorCode(). Most of\nthis code only cared if an error had been set via SetCanceled(), so this patch\nadds an atomic boolean mCanceled (and associated accessor GetCanceled()) that\ncan be used to the same effect but without acquiring the lock.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8754", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/TransportSecurityInfo.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b439431eb95b33e5619ac6c4cd07de948afe7b6", "parents": ["9a05c09af3770321c9d3acd89204ac62f3fb1878"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Gilbert \u003cjgilbert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499864 - WindowsNetworkFunctionsWrapper's dtor should be virtual. r=bagder\n\nAlso delete declaration of an unused var.\nBoth of these are compile warnings on win64 clang-cl.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: aOBmtxgpz6\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9029", "files": ["toolkit/system/windowsDHCPClient/DHCPUtils.cpp", "toolkit/system/windowsDHCPClient/WindowsNetworkFunctionsWrapper.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9e0a42364ef5fd6fd57d06a5df8113d34cb4b7f0", "parents": ["7b439431eb95b33e5619ac6c4cd07de948afe7b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Gilbert \u003cjgilbert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499858 - Re-enable MP4Demuxer.CENCFragVideo gtest for Windows. r=jya\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9030", "files": ["dom/media/gtest/TestMP4Demuxer.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d12de5ab68a2371f00fd20575f225ffeed8e41a0", "parents": ["9e0a42364ef5fd6fd57d06a5df8113d34cb4b7f0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499357 - Move inline script out of new aboutdebugging index.html;r=ladybenko\n\nThis preparatory work will be necessary to enable CSP for the new about\ndebugging.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8854", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/index.html", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/initializer.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "35b493a84e94f453975520a95b85145344d2fe70", "parents": ["d12de5ab68a2371f00fd20575f225ffeed8e41a0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-inbound to mozilla-central. a=merge", "files": ["browser/extensions/webcompat/bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/content/data/ua_overrides.jsm", "browser/extensions/webcompat/content/lib/ua_overrider.jsm", "browser/extensions/webcompat/install.rdf.in", "browser/extensions/webcompat/jar.mn", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/.eslintrc.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/browser.ini", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/browser_check_installed.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/browser_overrider.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/background.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/css/bug0000000-dummy-css-injection.css", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug0000000-dummy-js-injection.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1452707-window.controllers-shim-ib.absa.co.za.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1457335-histography.io-ua-change.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1472075-bankofamerica.com-ua-change.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1472081-election.gov.np-window.sidebar-shim.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1482066-portalminasnet.com-window.sidebar-shim.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/manifest.json", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/browser.dtd", "testing/mozharness/scripts/web_platform_tests.py", "testing/web-platform/meta/fetch/api/request/destination/fetch-destination.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/non-replaced-elements/tables/table-cell-width-s.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/non-replaced-elements/tables/table-width-s.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/non-replaced-elements/the-hr-element-0/width.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/replaced-elements/embedded-content-rendering-rules/canvas_without_context_a.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/quirks/historical/list-item-bullet-size.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/svg/shapes/rect-01.svg.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/svg/shapes/rect-02.svg.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "c0c288dc283e315982949e5d6565520f5872ab12", "parents": ["7b0a8e47d25608312af369290db040fa9009ddcf", "0ff0b54b9ec7c3e99acf8987b63995dbdce3e64a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland. a=merge", "files": ["browser/extensions/webcompat/bootstrap.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/content/data/ua_overrides.jsm", "browser/extensions/webcompat/content/lib/ua_overrider.jsm", "browser/extensions/webcompat/install.rdf.in", "browser/extensions/webcompat/jar.mn", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/.eslintrc.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/browser.ini", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/browser_check_installed.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/test/browser_overrider.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/background.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/css/bug0000000-dummy-css-injection.css", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug0000000-dummy-js-injection.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1452707-window.controllers-shim-ib.absa.co.za.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1457335-histography.io-ua-change.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1472075-bankofamerica.com-ua-change.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1472081-election.gov.np-window.sidebar-shim.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/injections/js/bug1482066-portalminasnet.com-window.sidebar-shim.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/webextension/manifest.json", "testing/web-platform/meta/fetch/api/request/destination/fetch-destination.https.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/non-replaced-elements/tables/table-cell-width-s.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/non-replaced-elements/tables/table-width-s.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/non-replaced-elements/the-hr-element-0/width.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/html/rendering/replaced-elements/embedded-content-rendering-rules/canvas_without_context_a.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/quirks/historical/list-item-bullet-size.html.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/svg/shapes/rect-01.svg.ini", "testing/web-platform/meta/svg/shapes/rect-02.svg.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "9ae0b64741cbf08fcd0ee6b031befd93fa10d184", "parents": ["35b493a84e94f453975520a95b85145344d2fe70", "c0c288dc283e315982949e5d6565520f5872ab12"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499209 - Refactor AccessibleWrap::ToBundle 1/2. r=Jamie\n\nThis refactor does a few things:\n1. Unifies the composition of the GeckoBundle, so that some tricky edge\ncases don't need to be implemented twice.\n2. Allows us to be more frugal with round trip sync ipc calls. Instead\nof retrieving everything from the start, only progressivley retrieve\nwhat we need.\n3. Sets the groundwork for the next patch that will return from this\nfunction earlier with a smaller bundle.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8778", "files": ["accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "89663382dd1e73388c69f7764b44baa9e20a33c2", "parents": ["9ae0b64741cbf08fcd0ee6b031befd93fa10d184"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499209 - Send abbreviated source bundles with accessibility events. r=Jamie\n\nDepends on D8778\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8779", "files": ["accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/SessionAccessibility.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7d3a598c12859f4bed3fc560bad3ae37af5f272a", "parents": ["89663382dd1e73388c69f7764b44baa9e20a33c2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris Pearce \u003ccpearce@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500251 - Add dummy pref with default value true, report via telemetry. r=mythmon\n\nThe Webrender Pref Experiment is reporting its pref via telemetry and that is\nreporting a different value than what the Normandy experiments telemetry\nindicates should be being seen.\n\nIn Bug 1499552 I added a pref and telemetry reporting in preparation for running\na dummy Pref Experiment to verify that prefs set are reported as set, but I\nrealised I missed a case; where there's an existing default pref set,\nwe're only covering the case where that default pref has value false. We're seeing\na ~25% failure rate in the pref reporting. So we should cover the other three cases\nin the dummy Pref Experiment, just in case it's one of these four cases that\nis failing.\n\nSo here I add another dummy pref with a default value of true, and I report that\nvia telemetry. I rename the pref I added yesterday to make things consistent.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9156", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/app/TelemetryEnvironment.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "38c1fc84fcaf42dbbdf53f286a0878cbadb0dbaf", "parents": ["7d3a598c12859f4bed3fc560bad3ae37af5f272a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kyle Machulis \u003ckyle@nonpolynomial.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1492648 - Move from nsDocShellLoadInfo to nsDocShellLoadState r=bzbarsky,nika\n\nCreates the nsDocShellLoadState object, which is basically\nnsDocShellLoadInfo plus a few extra fields to make it usable as a\nsingle argument to nsDocShell::LoadURI (and eventually\nnsDocShell::InternalLoad).\n\nSubframe history handling is a huge logic block in\nnsDocShell::LoadURI, which is only used on history loads. This patch\nalso extracts the logic out into its own function to make the body of\nLoadURI clearer.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D6944", "files": ["caps/NullPrincipal.cpp", "caps/NullPrincipal.h", "docshell/base/moz.build", "docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "docshell/base/nsDocShell.h", "docshell/base/nsDocShellLoadInfo.cpp", "docshell/base/nsDocShellLoadInfo.h", "docshell/base/nsDocShellLoadState.cpp", "docshell/base/nsDocShellLoadState.h", "docshell/base/nsDocShellLoadTypes.h", "docshell/base/nsIDocShell.idl", "docshell/shistory/nsSHEntry.cpp", "docshell/shistory/nsSHistory.cpp", "dom/base/Location.cpp", "dom/base/Location.h", "dom/base/nsFrameLoader.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.h", "dom/base/nsPIDOMWindow.h", "dom/clients/manager/ClientNavigateOpChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentChild.h", "dom/ipc/TabChild.cpp", "toolkit/components/windowcreator/nsIWindowProvider.idl", "toolkit/components/windowwatcher/nsPIWindowWatcher.idl", "toolkit/components/windowwatcher/nsWindowWatcher.cpp", "toolkit/components/windowwatcher/nsWindowWatcher.h", "xpfe/appshell/nsContentTreeOwner.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8dd09fad1f352d3814244908f0ea04f29fa2a307", "parents": ["38c1fc84fcaf42dbbdf53f286a0878cbadb0dbaf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "arthur.iakab \u003caiakab@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 7d3a598c1285 (bug 1499209),for Android build bustages on AccessibleWrap.cpp:416", "files": ["accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/SessionAccessibility.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "889b103b4e312bf7f0b407c0485bdd7c3e14e516", "parents": ["8dd09fad1f352d3814244908f0ea04f29fa2a307"], "tags": []}, {"author": "arthur.iakab \u003caiakab@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 89663382dd1e (bug 1499209),for Android build bustages on AccessibleWrap.cpp:416", "files": ["accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "74ce6fcac2111570473f580669c536d93f816133", "parents": ["889b103b4e312bf7f0b407c0485bdd7c3e14e516"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Robert Helmer \u003crhelmer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1492656 - move Telemetry Coverage ping in-tree r=janerik\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D6359", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "testing/profiles/common/user.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/app/TelemetryController.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/data/coverage-ping.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/moz.build", "toolkit/components/telemetry/pings/CoveragePing.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_CoveragePing.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b969cbe46b14814c397199ef84db2ed18d252107", "parents": ["74ce6fcac2111570473f580669c536d93f816133"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Aki Sasaki \u003casasaki@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499809 - l10n bumper should touch a status file on success. r=nthomas\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9017", "files": ["testing/mozharness/configs/l10n_bumper/jamun.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/l10n_bumper/mozilla-beta.py", "testing/mozharness/configs/l10n_bumper/mozilla-central.py", "testing/mozharness/scripts/l10n_bumper.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d0d593bf9772b1eb99547d114c9c6533e87bcd56", "parents": ["b969cbe46b14814c397199ef84db2ed18d252107"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499209 - Refactor AccessibleWrap::ToBundle 1/2. r=Jamie\n\nThis refactor does a few things:\n1. Unifies the composition of the GeckoBundle, so that some tricky edge\ncases don't need to be implemented twice.\n2. Allows us to be more frugal with round trip sync ipc calls. Instead\nof retrieving everything from the start, only progressivley retrieve\nwhat we need.\n3. Sets the groundwork for the next patch that will return from this\nfunction earlier with a smaller bundle.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8778", "files": ["accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4b8f36f9896b04d3e10f598383edd019feb1ce73", "parents": ["d0d593bf9772b1eb99547d114c9c6533e87bcd56"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eitan Isaacson \u003ceitan@monotonous.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499209 - Send abbreviated source bundles with accessibility events. r=Jamie\n\nDepends on D8778\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8779", "files": ["accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/SessionAccessibility.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "12527d50a493ce5a8c96bd7e6990d751ce9846e6", "parents": ["4b8f36f9896b04d3e10f598383edd019feb1ce73"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Holbert \u003cdholbert@cs.stanford.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499542 part 1: Don't do early-freeze of flexible-but-doomed-to-be-clamped flex items, if devtools are active.  r=bradwerth\n\nWe'd like to be able to record the \"desired\" (pre-clamped) delta size from\ntentatively flexing for these items.  That size would be computed during a loop\nof the flex layout algorithm -- but we can't do that if we freeze them before\nwe start flexing. So let's bypass this early freeze so they get a chance to\ncompute this tentative size, even though they can never have it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8922", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFlexContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "52bd865d757c2787845e1bb79ed3936484d6ce3b", "parents": ["12527d50a493ce5a8c96bd7e6990d751ce9846e6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Holbert \u003cdholbert@cs.stanford.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499542 part 2: Skip frozen flex items when recording grow-vs-shrink state and deltas. r=bradwerth\n\nFrozen flex items have already been clamped to their min/max sizes, so their\nsize-change isn't a \"how much we want to flex\" measurement, and it's not useful\nfor determining whether the rest of the line is shrinking.\n\nThis patch is just adding a `if (!item-\u003eIsFrozen())` check around some code,\nand reindenting that code, and adjusting a few comments.\n\nThis change is necessary to avoid failing the \"GrowthState\" assertions,\nbecause (for example) a flex item that's clamped to a small max-width\ncould fool us into thinking we're in a \"shrinking\" state (since its final\nsize is smaller than its base size), even though really we're\nin a \"growth\" state and the item was simply clamped.  We avoid this\nproblem by skipping (potentially-clamped) frozen items when determining\nthe line's GrowthState.\n\nDepends on D8922\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9018", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFlexContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3ea646bde4de4772a439a31798406287d2be685e", "parents": ["52bd865d757c2787845e1bb79ed3936484d6ce3b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Holbert \u003cdholbert@cs.stanford.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499542 part 3: Give test_flex_items.html an item that's trivially clamped to small max-size. r=bradwerth\n\nDepends on D9018\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9019", "files": ["dom/flex/test/chrome/test_flex_items.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ce0ac92bee586c4e67a302929e1532ec8831505", "parents": ["3ea646bde4de4772a439a31798406287d2be685e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "arthur.iakab \u003caiakab@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset b969cbe46b14 (bug 1492656)for Android xpcshell failures on unit/test_CoveragePing.js CLOSED TREE", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "testing/profiles/common/user.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/app/TelemetryController.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/docs/data/coverage-ping.rst", "toolkit/components/telemetry/moz.build", "toolkit/components/telemetry/pings/CoveragePing.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_CoveragePing.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c096376198dfd61024c75345b94c9674b403988b", "parents": ["2ce0ac92bee586c4e67a302929e1532ec8831505"], "tags": []}, {"author": "arthur.iakab \u003caiakab@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 2 changesets (bug 1499209)for failing  Android geckoview on AccessibilityTest.testCheckbox\n\nBacked out changeset 12527d50a493 (bug 1499209)\nBacked out changeset 4b8f36f9896b (bug 1499209)", "files": ["accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/AccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.cpp", "accessible/android/ProxyAccessibleWrap.h", "accessible/android/SessionAccessibility.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f972dce0b524da3bb82a07d3c4c04d693941c878", "parents": ["c096376198dfd61024c75345b94c9674b403988b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nick Thomas \u003cnthomas@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500274 - increase timeouts for Windows nightly builds, r=RyanVM (irc), a=RyanVM", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/build/windows.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fdd2d783dd2e354ab9dae7d04912cd6b937ba9b3", "parents": ["c0c288dc283e315982949e5d6565520f5872ab12"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 7a7d5508f873 (bug 1494537) as requested by tcampbell on irc for causing crashes in bug 1500285, 1500255. a=backout", "files": ["js/src/builtin/Array.cpp", "js/src/builtin/Array.h", "js/src/jit-test/tests/cacheir/bug1494537.js", "js/src/jit/BaselineCacheIRCompiler.cpp", "js/src/jit/CacheIR.cpp", "js/src/jit/CacheIR.h", "js/src/jit/CacheIRCompiler.cpp", "js/src/jit/CacheIRCompiler.h", "js/src/jit/IonCacheIRCompiler.cpp", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.cpp", "js/src/jit/VMFunctions.h", "js/src/vm/NativeObject.cpp", "js/src/vm/NativeObject.h", "js/src/vm/Shape.h", "js/src/vm/ShapedObject.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6c55991a052eca284abb6d0a7980765e718e8f02", "parents": ["fdd2d783dd2e354ab9dae7d04912cd6b937ba9b3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge m-c to autoland. a=merge", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/cacheir/bug1494537.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "b73ac3a4b55d78e5394b77b80b2447b6066e9078", "parents": ["f972dce0b524da3bb82a07d3c4c04d693941c878", "6c55991a052eca284abb6d0a7980765e718e8f02"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brendan Dahl \u003cbdahl@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1486888 - Support XUL broadcasters in non-XUL documents. r=smaug\n\nThe majority of the XUL broadcaster logic is moved out of XULDocument and\ninto a separate class (XULBroadcastManager). The hookup points for when\nlisteners need to be created and listeners need to be notified is now\nhandled by the XULElement itself and nsDocument. To avoid any overhead,\nthe XULBroadcastManager is only ever created when a document uses a\nlistener.\n\nThe new approach does have the disadvantage that broadcasting can now only\nwork with XULElements, but going forward we'd like to discontinue this\nfeature and rely on MutationObservers to implement similar things.\n\nOne test had to be modified to use XUL elements instead of HTML elements\nbecause of the reason noted above.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8888", "files": ["dom/base/nsDocument.cpp", "dom/base/nsIDocument.h", "dom/xul/XULBroadcastManager.cpp", "dom/xul/XULBroadcastManager.h", "dom/xul/XULDocument.cpp", "dom/xul/XULDocument.h", "dom/xul/moz.build", "dom/xul/nsXULElement.cpp", "dom/xul/nsXULElement.h", "dom/xul/test/test_bug445177.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "394a1e5544f65e59ea1e12e19f788f50078ddf20", "parents": ["b73ac3a4b55d78e5394b77b80b2447b6066e9078"], "tags": []}, {"author": "June Wilde \u003cjewilde@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1458129 - Prevent double free in mar_sign.c. r=rstrong\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8924", "files": ["modules/libmar/sign/mar_sign.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "379d79841c5d439654d77f264f7c9d730863059e", "parents": ["0ff0b54b9ec7c3e99acf8987b63995dbdce3e64a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mihai Tabara \u003cmtabara@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1475101 - add mark-as-started task. r=rail a=release", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-mark-as-started/kind.yml", "taskcluster/docs/kinds.rst", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/release_mark_as_started.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/task.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/scriptworker.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e87d7028568e721e8d297ce62f9622e74d29bb37", "parents": ["379d79841c5d439654d77f264f7c9d730863059e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lars T Hansen \u003clhansen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1495731 - remove JS_VOLATILE_ARM, it is no longer relevant.  r=waldo\n\nJS_VOLATILE_ARM was a workaround for a gcc 4.7 bug on B2G where it\nwould generate unaligned word accesses that should have been\nindividual byte accesses.  We now require at least gcc 6.1 (and ARM\nsystems support unaligned accesses).", "files": ["js/src/vm/TypedArrayObject-inl.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bb430eaf5521aa8ab233a45b585ff9e5dfecf4c9", "parents": ["e87d7028568e721e8d297ce62f9622e74d29bb37"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lars T Hansen \u003clhansen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1496582 - add required flags to bulk memory/table operations.  r=jseward\n\nThe encodings are specified at the very bottom of\nhttps://github.com/WebAssembly/bulk-memory-operations/blob/master/proposals/bulk-memory-operations/Overview.md\n\nI have opted to call the byte memOrTableFlags because that is the\nmeaning it will eventually have, even though currently the spec calls\nit a \"memory\" (even when the subject is a table).", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/wasm/passive-segs-nonboundary.js", "js/src/wasm/WasmOpIter.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmTextToBinary.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fe962bfc351a0f198e3fa990693973eee5fbcf81", "parents": ["bb430eaf5521aa8ab233a45b585ff9e5dfecf4c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lars T Hansen \u003clhansen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500120 - fix compiler state for struct.narrow.  r=bbouvier\n\nThis makes sure that the compiler's view of the stack matches the run-time stack\nwhen we generate code for struct.narrow.  The bug crept in here because I\ninsisted on generating an in-line test for null before calling out to the\ninstance.  But this is unnecessary; the code in the instance can do this just\nfine, and null is not a common case here.  (And struct.narrow is extremely slow\nin any case, as it's just prototype code)\n\nSo, move the null check to C++ and generate straight-line code in Rabaldr.", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmBaselineCompile.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmInstance.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmInstance.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a25a1dd8a9f58ee74fe2922c0611d3013be00091", "parents": ["fe962bfc351a0f198e3fa990693973eee5fbcf81"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mihai Tabara \u003cmtabara@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499440 - add esr60/release configs for mark-as-star