he timeout for Windows opt builds to 3hr to match other PGO-enabled builds. r=me, a=release", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/build/windows.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aba25ceab10f829e07c36ab1fd9fdbb83d4774c2", "parents": ["8caddcd5d619634e7a1b55b96a7fabc645e9db74"], "tags": []}], "date": 1540212484, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10015": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e e7d16b72571e\nbr -\u003e 0e2097cce6ab\ncy -\u003e d1367498cb71\ndsb -\u003e e3284bb3c0fc\nhsb -\u003e be2bf5799d82\nlt -\u003e 4251c53c2ce2", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9f819e19c3f77259b1cd8c3b381e35b6da10f5c2", "parents": ["aba25ceab10f829e07c36ab1fd9fdbb83d4774c2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e e7d16b72571e\nbr -\u003e 0e2097cce6ab\ncs -\u003e b087b1fe4b6f\ncy -\u003e d1367498cb71\ndsb -\u003e e3284bb3c0fc\nhsb -\u003e be2bf5799d82\npt-PT -\u003e dab487f3bc2d\nsl -\u003e 0090399b30f4\ntr -\u003e 3935b651d952\nzh-CN -\u003e 0f2a2b362d31", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "284e3bfdc49fd93aa49b2e15c19129243189fdef", "parents": ["9f819e19c3f77259b1cd8c3b381e35b6da10f5c2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1540213226, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10016": {"changesets": [{"author": "Marco Zehe \u003cmzehe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1492393 - Make our table index methods aware of cells spanning multiple columns, r=surkov\n\nSometimes, when cells have display:block, and a different cell in the same row has a column span, our index methods did not take these into account. Also, when regular tables encounter such a cell, index calculation failed.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D7867", "files": ["accessible/generic/ARIAGridAccessible.cpp", "accessible/generic/TableAccessible.cpp", "accessible/html/HTMLTableAccessible.cpp", "accessible/tests/mochitest/table/test_indexes_table.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "295644de04d2b1abbccd102473cbf3023dfce21a", "parents": ["1030155f208e08a4a4673655c8b6b343c1b920a1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500136 - Use openTrustedLinkIn in gStoragePressureObserver. r=jaws\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9125", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fbb784c460e5fdc034e1e734fe5d5cfcd3c18c33", "parents": ["295644de04d2b1abbccd102473cbf3023dfce21a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexandre Poirot \u003cpoirot.alex@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500070 - Avoid using about:debugging in generic about: page tests. r=jdescottes\n\nOpening about:debugging may lead to pending listAddons requests.\nTests that open about:debugging should be careful to wait for the end\nof these requests, which this test doesn't do.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6YyfdW78kOS\n\nDepends on D8828\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8867", "files": ["browser/components/contextualidentity/test/browser/browser_aboutURLs.js", "devtools/client/shared/test/browser_link.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "33e352068e35a538ff380ef30749e53946c5bdd3", "parents": ["fbb784c460e5fdc034e1e734fe5d5cfcd3c18c33"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alexandre Poirot \u003cpoirot.alex@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500068 - Avoid opening Add-ons panel when a location hash is passed to select another one. r=jdescottes\n\nDoing this avoid loading the addons panel and doing its related requests,\nwhich may still be pending after closing about:debugging.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LJjaE5YVgXi\n\nDepends on D8867\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8868", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging/components/Aboutdebugging.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "14a6f6ecebc25ee188d852a4b12ed3befba3580a", "parents": ["33e352068e35a538ff380ef30749e53946c5bdd3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Patrick Brosset \u003cpbrosset@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497178 - Hide the flex outline for 0-sized items; r=rcaliman\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8969", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/flexbox/components/FlexItemSizingOutline.js", "devtools/client/inspector/flexbox/components/FlexItemSizingProperties.js", "devtools/client/inspector/flexbox/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/flexbox/test/browser_flexbox_item_outline_hidden_when_useless.js", "devtools/client/themes/layout.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0927741e9110eebe9d55a73f97fd8bb47f2d6bff", "parents": ["14a6f6ecebc25ee188d852a4b12ed3befba3580a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brian Grinstead \u003cbgrinstead@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500240 - Use getAnonymousElementByAttribute instead of getElementByID for XBL anonymous search element;r=dao\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9150", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_urlbarSearchSuggestions_opt-out.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "53abc33e3e38ea49862e20af8974bb5f8a17f439", "parents": ["0927741e9110eebe9d55a73f97fd8bb47f2d6bff"], "tags": []}, {"author": "rosston \u003cross.brandes@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1389221 - Add readline navigation bindings to url bar on macOS r=dao\n\nSupport ctrl-n and ctrl-p for navigating down and up (respectively) in the url\nbar on macOS. The autocomplete widget will also support the same key bindings.\nThis functionality matches ctrl-n/ctrl-p behavior on the other major macOS\nbrowsers.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D6451", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_autocomplete_readline_navigation.js", "browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml", "toolkit/content/widgets/autocomplete.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "14e469a4365b820bfb1a890c6993edb118a60d4f", "parents": ["53abc33e3e38ea49862e20af8974bb5f8a17f439"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan Hendrickson \u003cryan.hendrickson@alum.mit.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1419947 - Extend tabbrowser to track and use tab successors; r=dao\n\nThe successor of a tab is similar to the owner of a tab, in that if an active\ntab is closed, the successor will be activated next. The differences are that\nsuccessor always defaults to being unset (an extension can set it through a\nnot-yet-implemented API), whereas tabbrowser sets owner to be the opener of\nbackground tabs; successor is always consulted when an active tab is closed,\nwhereas the use of owner is gated by a pref; and when a tab is closed, hidden,\nor moved to another window, any tabs whose successor is the affected tab\ninherit that tab's successor, whereas in the parallel situation with owners,\nthe owner of such tabs is simply set to null.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D4731", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js", "browser/base/content/test/tabs/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/tabs/browser_tabSuccessors.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15fd39e497668c53ee7fecd914510c5f4ac35bf7", "parents": ["14e469a4365b820bfb1a890c6993edb118a60d4f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Wes Kocher \u003cwkocher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499904 - Update expectation data for cookies/samesite/form-post-blank-reload.html r=jgraham\n\nThe test it already failing on desktop, but fennec fails differently.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9191", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/cookies/samesite/form-post-blank-reload.html.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "929617c0f367c6fe1b8751dbcca043235490494e", "parents": ["15fd39e497668c53ee7fecd914510c5f4ac35bf7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Polly Shaw \u003cpolly.shaw@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1495024 - Firefox does not use exponential back-off after failing to load a PAC file. r=bagder\n\nThis patch addresses a bug introduced in the solution to Bug 356831, in which\nthe back-off time for reloading PAC files was set to the shortest interval every time a failure happened, thus auto-detecting PAC every 5 seconds\non a network on which WPAD did not resolve when the proxy was set to auto-detect.\nThe changes in this patch are:\n * nsPACMan.h - declares a private overload to LoadPACFromURI, with an\n additional parameter called aResetLoadFailureCount.\n * nsPACMan.cpp - moves the implementation of the old LoadPACFromURI to the new\n private overload, with the modification that the mLoadFailureCount field\n is only reset to 0 if aResetLoadFailureCount is true. Replaces the\n implementation of the public LoadPACFromURI with a call to the private overload\n with aResetLoadFailureCount = true. Also replaces the call made from within\n nsPACMan when triggering an internal reload with a call with\n aResetLoadFailureCount = false, thus ensuring that internally triggered reloads\n do not reset the back-off time.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9035", "files": ["netwerk/base/nsPACMan.cpp", "netwerk/base/nsPACMan.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ab0725fa9dc15ce3e3d8c0c15f63df516cdd12cd", "parents": ["929617c0f367c6fe1b8751dbcca043235490494e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bel\u00e9n Albeza \u003cbalbeza@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1496400 - Remove common.css r=jdescottes,daisuke\n\n- Removed common.css\n- Re-ordered the loading of stylesheets, so components sheets are loaded _after_ the more generic rules\n- Refactored some of our components into more generic ones.\n\nNote that a few styles do not match exactly `common.css` (for instance, buttons' `min-height` and `min-width`), in favor of Photon. This might change later depending on the UX guidance we'll get eventually.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8970", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/aboutdebugging.css", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/index.html", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/base.css", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/App.css", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/RuntimeInfo.css", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/RuntimeInfo.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/connect/ConnectPage.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/connect/ConnectSection.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/connect/NetworkLocationsForm.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/connect/NetworkLocationsList.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/DebugTargetItem.css", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/DebugTargetPane.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/InspectAction.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/ServiceWorkerAction.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/TemporaryExtensionAction.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/TemporaryExtensionInstaller.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/WorkerDetail.css", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/debugtarget/WorkerDetail.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/sidebar/Sidebar.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/sidebar/SidebarItem.css", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/components/sidebar/SidebarRuntimeItem.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5ba65c3ad1ffc76c31dcfda165b87afc1269b415", "parents": ["ab0725fa9dc15ce3e3d8c0c15f63df516cdd12cd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Patrick Brosset \u003cpbrosset@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500110 - Improve the debuggin intermittents documentation; r=sole\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9114", "files": ["devtools/docs/tests/debugging-intermittents.md"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "95679778f4ed58a60e3c5befcb99a9f38661234a", "parents": ["5ba65c3ad1ffc76c31dcfda165b87afc1269b415"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ahilya Sinha \u003cahilyasinha99@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Use testfile mtimes to pre-filter files iterated over for the manifest update, r=ato\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8221", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/commands.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/item.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/manifest.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/tests/test_manifest.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/update.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/vcs.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5e3b8ad4c8f42342d9d16723236261501aafd040", "parents": ["95679778f4ed58a60e3c5befcb99a9f38661234a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Update the .gitignore file, r=ato\n\nDepends on D8221\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8222", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/.gitignore"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9afac925aef8a815e674ffb2e56c4220f7913004", "parents": ["5e3b8ad4c8f42342d9d16723236261501aafd040"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Allow the gitignore filter to work on name components only, r=ato\n\nWe end up with a lot of rules like (?:.*)/.*\\.ext which are basically\ntrying to find the last component in a path and match against\nthat. These are rather slow to run so the easiest thing tdo is just\npass in the last component of the path when we know that's the only\nthing the rule can match.\n\nThe changes to surrounding code to use this API will be made in future\ncommits.\n\nDepends on D8222\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8223", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/gitignore/gitignore.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/manifest.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/testloader.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a6a89509add7962cae05fc9b7e504c42910a7147", "parents": ["9afac925aef8a815e674ffb2e56c4220f7913004"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Update the gitignore implementation to work as an iterator filter, r=ato\n\nThis updates the gitignore implemenation to take input like os.walk\nbut with additional stat data for the files. It also makes several\nuseful optimistaions:\n\n * Avoid using regex when just matching a literal\n * Identify patterns that can only match the final component of a path\n   and run those against that component rather than the full path.\n * Add the possibility of providing a dictionary of paths to gitignore\n   statuses as a cache.\n\nThis dramatically reduces the amount of time we spend in gitignore\nprocessing when updating the manifest.\n\nDepends on D8223\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8224", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/gitignore/gitignore.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/gitignore/tests/test_gitignore.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c3cb0408498cd890dba6038de0debf247ba03324", "parents": ["a6a89509add7962cae05fc9b7e504c42910a7147"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Update the lint to the new gitignore API, r=ato\n\nDepends on D8224\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8225", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/lint/lint.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "184bc31c33a6edba5ddb13d1daef81c39f87370f", "parents": ["c3cb0408498cd890dba6038de0debf247ba03324"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Add manifest caches for the mtime and gitignore rules, r=ato\n\nWhen processing the manifest using the worktree, instead of reading\nall files to see if the content changed, instead only process files where\nthe mtime has been updated since the previous run. Also cache the\nresult of running gitignore, so we can save a couple of seconds\nprocessing the gitignore rules.\n\nDepends on D8225\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8226", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/vcs.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "48be184d5377dd0aee94eca7ef5a3c4d369069c1", "parents": ["184bc31c33a6edba5ddb13d1daef81c39f87370f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Add a custom implementation of os.walk, r=ato\n\nCompared to the normal os.walk this has a couple of differences:\n\n* It returns lists of (name, stat) for filenames and directories,\n  allowing callers to reuse the stat data without going back to the\n  system to re-request it.\n\n* Directories are always returned as paths relative to the root, and\n  the root itself is returned as the empty string.\n\n* It is non-recursive.\n\nThere are also a few features missing that aren't required for our use\ncases.\n\nDepends on D8226\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8227", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/lint/tests/test_lint.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/vcs.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2caa5633dea13f347932979888fc3424f50c4c77", "parents": ["48be184d5377dd0aee94eca7ef5a3c4d369069c1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Fix the cache lifecycle, r=ato\n\nThe caches weren't being invalidated when the manifest itself\nchanged. To fix this the manifest itself has to be written before the\ncache and the cache has to include data about the manifest that it's\nassociated with (the mtime and path are used for this purpose).\n\nTo make all this work requires a single method that can load the\nmanifest, update it, write the manifest and write the\ncaches. Therefore we introduce a single load_and_update method that is\nintended to replace all previous use of the load() or update() methods\n(and as a bonus handles manifest version mismatches in a single\nplace).\n\nDepends on D8227\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8228", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/gitignore/gitignore.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/item.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/manifest.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/update.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/manifest/vcs.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wpt/testfiles.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/testloader.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/tests/test_update.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c482d18cc0507e202e004238c15a3bb30b64a837", "parents": ["2caa5633dea13f347932979888fc3424f50c4c77"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Fix the .gitignore rules, r=ato\n\nDepends on D8228\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8229", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/.gitignore"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3a9a7760db5c9e1bf584657ef14f1afbdeee5a91", "parents": ["c482d18cc0507e202e004238c15a3bb30b64a837"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Pass the manifest file directly into wpttest.from_manifest, r=ato\n\nDepends on D8229\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8230", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wpt/testfiles.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/testloader.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/tests/test_wpttest.py", "testing/web-platform/tests/tools/wptrunner/wptrunner/wpttest.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7bba4d617db672ba06b026f3f5d9e067e0c01d0d", "parents": ["3a9a7760db5c9e1bf584657ef14f1afbdeee5a91"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Update manifest before tests, r=ato\n\nDepends on D8230\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8231", "files": ["testing/web-platform/tests/tools/ci/ci_wptrunner_infrastructure.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "22a06c8c8dc6ea3a7413904dc486eb2bc2ac2f92", "parents": ["7bba4d617db672ba06b026f3f5d9e067e0c01d0d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1497898 - Update gecko wpt manifest update to use caches, r=ato\n\nDepends on D8231\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8232", "files": ["testing/web-platform/mach_commands_base.py", "testing/web-platform/manifestupdate.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "57877c614829ff051ed0e2b66f895292e904b207", "parents": ["22a06c8c8dc6ea3a7413904dc486eb2bc2ac2f92"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500121 - Give IdValueVector some inline capacity. r=luke\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9117", "files": ["js/src/ds/IdValuePair.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d46116aa35273c5da6a5970ee683fedaa81dd628", "parents": ["57877c614829ff051ed0e2b66f895292e904b207"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500080 - UrlbarInput::value getter should return the untrimmed value. r=mak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9088", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f6c89db3520cca62fc39ec0915beecf5e9a22278", "parents": ["d46116aa35273c5da6a5970ee683fedaa81dd628"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500242 - [marionette] Don't modify DEFAULT_SHUTDOWN_TIMEOUT constant. r=ato\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9227", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_quit_restart.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9645a734546be91c08cdba441d7003259e51bda8", "parents": ["f6c89db3520cca62fc39ec0915beecf5e9a22278"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500242 - [marionette] Obey the extended shutdown timeout for Firefox ASAN builds. r=ato\n\nFirefox uses different shutdown timeouts for the terminator thread\ndepending on the build type. For opt/debug builds this will be 60s,\nwhile for ASAN builds 180s are used.\n\nCurrently Marionette only takes the 60s into account, and always\nkills the binary after 70s if a shutdown hasn't happened by that\ntime. This actually prevents the background hang monitor to kill\nFirefox for ASAN builds, and to report a meaningful crash report\nfor the shutdown hang.\n\nTo inform clients about the correct shutdown timeout, a new vendor\nspecific capability with the name `moz:shutdownTimeout` is used as\npart of the new session capabilities.\n\nDepends on D9227\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9228", "files": ["testing/marionette/capabilities.js", "testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_quit_restart.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a2be0efbc4c4f1931f39a1dfe4a082cec09b2e0", "parents": ["9645a734546be91c08cdba441d7003259e51bda8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500086 - While typing, show the Go button and hide the history dropmarker. r=mak\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9106", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarInput.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59fed9e69c53f229e240d0bdfb0b5ca2d3afeb67", "parents": ["9a2be0efbc4c4f1931f39a1dfe4a082cec09b2e0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 12 changesets (bug 1497898) for build bustages. CLOSED TREE\n\nBacked out changeset 57877c614829 (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset 22a06c8c8dc6 (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset 7bba4d617db6 (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset 3a9a7760db5c (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset c482d18cc050 (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset 2caa5633dea1 (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset 48be184d5377 (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset 184bc31c33a6 (bug 1497898)\nBacked out changeset c3c