nl -\u003e 46ac24ad12bb\npl -\u003e ad6ef4707dad\ntr -\u003e 7c94f0fe3319", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bbbb6d06a855b7d7b9e0a283aed9bbf97a772680", "parents": ["0af5b6b540febc8c5b4cd07904fbf0a2b80f15ea"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541523635, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10123": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\neo -\u003e 3533e235b455\nfr -\u003e 7a82101747dd\npt-BR -\u003e a5e7cd01df14\npt-PT -\u003e 74a6e70d26bb\nsv-SE -\u003e 14d2265d3450", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3ee4dbe0ee20f2d3ea3e2f27d10298f4a0bc15ec", "parents": ["bbbb6d06a855b7d7b9e0a283aed9bbf97a772680"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbn-BD -\u003e 45495d9dd16e\neo -\u003e 3533e235b455\nfr -\u003e 7a82101747dd\npt-BR -\u003e a5e7cd01df14\npt-PT -\u003e 74a6e70d26bb\nsv-SE -\u003e d2129d9feb4b", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a9fd33c4797167c9b3a028d4eaefe3af97b77703", "parents": ["3ee4dbe0ee20f2d3ea3e2f27d10298f4a0bc15ec"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541530823, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10124": {"changesets": [{"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1453895 - Avoid reftest startup hang waiting for focus. r=jmaher, a=test-only\n\nIntermittently, at least on Windows, reftest.jsm finds that the reftest.xul\nwindow is not focused on startup; focus seems to be on the dummy about:blank\nwindow. This patch tries to detect that condition and correct it by bringing\nreftest.xul (g.containingWindow) into focus before specifically focusing\nthe browser element (g.browser).", "files": ["layout/tools/reftest/reftest.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "afe2dac07dff453b0a69151f0a7367dea0d5bf3e", "parents": ["a9fd33c4797167c9b3a028d4eaefe3af97b77703"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504807 - [marionette] Remove call to non-existent \"Marionette:newSession\" message listener. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10998", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2dba15f946e31610e6f6c07b647d59184866f5f7", "parents": ["afe2dac07dff453b0a69151f0a7367dea0d5bf3e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504807 - [marionette] Don't remove pending command unless it has been completed. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nWith the use of multiple content processes in Firefox a navigation\ncommand can cause the active framescript to be moved to a different\nprocess. This interrupts the currently executed command, and as such\nneeds to be executed again after the framescript has been finished\ninitializing.\n\nCurrently flushing the pending commands doesn't take into account\nthat the framescript can even be moved multiple times to a different\nprocess during a single page navigation. As such all pending commands\nare getting removed after the first process move. For navigation\ncommands this means that no page load listeners are attached for\nsubsequent process changes, and navigation commands could never\nreturn, and cause a hang of Marionette.\n\nTo solve the problem the pending commands need to be flushed each\ntime the process changes. They will remove themselves from the list\nonce they have finished processing.\n\nDepends on D10998\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10999", "files": ["testing/marionette/browser.js", "testing/marionette/driver.js", "testing/marionette/listener.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6900e33d73082d4dd29a9efa1737e1b29af52c52", "parents": ["2dba15f946e31610e6f6c07b647d59184866f5f7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1488826 - [marionette] Disable content blocking introduction panel. r=ato, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11007", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/geckoinstance.py", "testing/marionette/components/marionette.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5b42d14602aacbaf0aa2bbdcbfb7cf2100cb162e", "parents": ["6900e33d73082d4dd29a9efa1737e1b29af52c52"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541598345, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10125": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nico Grunbaum \u003cna-g@nostrum.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1457129 - Correct WebRTC getStats WPT to wait for remote stats before comparing. r=jib, a=test-only\n\nIf care is not taken to wait for remote stats on senders and receivers, then the contents\nof the stats reports will not be stable. Waiting for this stability should fix our\nintermittent failures checking that RTCRtpSender/Receiver.getStats() returns the\nsame dictionaries that RTCPeerConnection.getStats(sender/receiver.track) does.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D5804", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/webrtc/RTCPeerConnection-helper.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/webrtc/RTCPeerConnection-track-stats.https.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f1f32b76f7ee4fa06d9ad1e7a7929554293f48a", "parents": ["5b42d14602aacbaf0aa2bbdcbfb7cf2100cb162e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Raphael Pierzina \u003crpierzina@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500298 - Refactor TelemetryTestCase and add logging. r=Dexter,whimboo, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10581", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/marionette/harness/telemetry_harness/testcase.py", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/marionette/tests/client/test_main_tab_scalars.py", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/marionette/tests/unit/test_ping_server_received_ping.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9ca3d0b3e93a8561ad1f18bcdace54e73f025ecc", "parents": ["2f1f32b76f7ee4fa06d9ad1e7a7929554293f48a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Geoff Brown \u003cgbrown@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503687 - Avoid python attribute errors for some infrequent xpcshell timeouts. r=jmaher, a=test-only", "files": ["testing/xpcshell/runxpcshelltests.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7943fd2406300abe14a6aedbae8eb5c1d988443e", "parents": ["9ca3d0b3e93a8561ad1f18bcdace54e73f025ecc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541598937, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10126": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gabriele Svelto \u003cgsvelto@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498942 - Lengthen timeouts for detecting hung content processes during shutdown r=Ehsan a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10621", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.h", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b925d9a30ccb4e020f4dc8ef5a7d24e2b5dcbfa", "parents": ["7943fd2406300abe14a6aedbae8eb5c1d988443e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502080 - Freeze the sort order of about:performance for 5s when the mouse is moved, r=felipe a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/components/aboutperformance/content/aboutPerformance.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0c7a40a87b9a29236ac5fc30bad547177591cbb8", "parents": ["0b925d9a30ccb4e020f4dc8ef5a7d24e2b5dcbfa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504709 - Freeze the sort order of about:performance for 5s on click events, r=felipe a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/components/aboutperformance/content/aboutPerformance.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7d121c076bc72759290367bc86a18e995c8716a4", "parents": ["0c7a40a87b9a29236ac5fc30bad547177591cbb8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505031 - stop using the global 'event' object in about:performance, r=felipe a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/components/aboutperformance/content/aboutPerformance.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4bf79d20c6444193ca12af354163c448d81a1f44", "parents": ["7d121c076bc72759290367bc86a18e995c8716a4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502440 - Hide browser internals in about:performance for beta and release users, r=felipe a=jcristau", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js", "toolkit/components/aboutperformance/content/aboutPerformance.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "61362de96df954b728a8a9787e1839bc8b15dbc1", "parents": ["4bf79d20c6444193ca12af354163c448d81a1f44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Qu\u00e8ze \u003cflorian@queze.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502437 - Hide system add-ons in about:performance when browser internals are hidden, r=felipe a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/components/aboutperformance/content/aboutPerformance.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "02f3ab06c2eb5abc97b49c12d3702d50c439526f", "parents": ["61362de96df954b728a8a9787e1839bc8b15dbc1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541600096, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "10127": {"changesets": [{"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502638 - Make use of the position passed in to AndroidVelocityTracker::StartTracking(). r=kats a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10448", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AndroidVelocityTracker.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ab7f1db24dde0647fbe476237b6684a5201f07cb", "parents": ["02f3ab06c2eb5abc97b49c12d3702d50c439526f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502638 - Guard against two samples with the same timestamp in AndroidVelocityTracker. r=kats a=jcristau\n\nDepends on D10448\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10449", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AndroidVelocityTracker.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "035ea5732599008612558e023ba5e84d43e43fd9", "parents": ["ab7f1db24dde0647fbe476237b6684a5201f07cb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Botond Ballo \u003cbotond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502638 - If the velocity tracker can't compute a velocity, zero out the axis velocity. r=kats a=jcristau\n\nThe previous value of the axis velocity could be stale, e.g. in the opposite\ndirection.\n\nDepends on D10449\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10450", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/Axis.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "063b9e4ccceb439d3ec795da08924c6a70f9cd6f", "parents": ["035ea5732599008612558e023ba5e84d43e43fd9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Errolyn \u003csam@fishy.ninja\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1493192: Flip order of sent/unsent crashes on about:crashes r=mconley a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10526", "files": ["toolkit/crashreporter/content/crashes.xhtml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0bf8a52ad207c50853d48a1ba11999f5f67b2a54", "parents": ["063b9e4ccceb439d3ec795da08924c6a70f9cd6f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dana Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1496736 - check if we actually have a new key DB before removing the old one r=jcj a=jcristau\n\nIn bug 1475775, we added code to remove the old NSS key DB if the user has set a\npassword on the grounds that the old DB could potentially be unencrypted and\ncontain secrets. However, we did so with the assumption that we were using the\nnew DB, which is not necessarily true when the system has been configured to\nalways use the old DB, as with some RedHat products. This patch checks for the\nexistence of the new DB before proceeding with deleting the old DB. Technically\nthis isn't sufficient, because the new DB could be present even if we're not\nusing it. However, we've already gone far into \"this configuration isn't\nsupported\" territory.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9318", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/nsNSSComponent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1370c2a23ff7a681191c40ca9bd744b7597a3a75", "parents": ["0bf8a52ad207c50853d48a1ba11999f5f67b2a54"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1501699 - Don't consume the Ctrl+Shift+Tab event when not actually handling it. r=jaws a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11024", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-ctrlTab.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "663b37581fef75a2e7f0ee66218062c45ebf5944", "parents": ["1370c2a23ff7a681191c40ca9bd744b7597a3a75"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541600639, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "10128": {"changesets": [{"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503306 - Properly set accentcolor and textcolor properties for Light and Dark themes. r=ntim a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10542", "files": ["browser/components/nsBrowserGlue.js", "browser/themes/linux/compacttheme.css", "browser/themes/osx/compacttheme.css", "browser/themes/shared/compacttheme.inc.css", "browser/themes/windows/compacttheme.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "17c2c58a532880c11105c6f75df5c07eafe5c589", "parents": ["663b37581fef75a2e7f0ee66218062c45ebf5944"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504725 - Explicitly pass event to language change handler r=jaws a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10924", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2b9ec060ca1aac2f6992607b2b4f4df683802faf", "parents": ["17c2c58a532880c11105c6f75df5c07eafe5c589"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505069 - Stop abusing --lwt-text-color in the Contextual Feature Recommendation popup-notification. r=Mardak a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11055", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/browser.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f9e1cbdcab70d1dd4b4441bec785b07e12485e09", "parents": ["2b9ec060ca1aac2f6992607b2b4f4df683802faf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1471671 - Avoid crash with WebRender when the scroll metadata is unavailable. r=kats a=jcristau\n\nWe are seeing crash reports in the wild where there is no scroll\nmetadata available for an ASR for a display item and its clip. It\nappears that in the non-WR path, it skips such items, so we should\nprobably do the same thing with WebRender. If the scrolling ends up\nbeing wrong, hopefully a reproducible use case will make its way to use\nto further debug, as the crash reports have not yielded anything to date.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D9699", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/ClipManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d29760cf44dd39a8716e5557329df863d0ccd91c", "parents": ["f9e1cbdcab70d1dd4b4441bec785b07e12485e09"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502454 - Ensure we are consistent in how we define and use scroll IDs with WebRender. r=kats a=jcristau\n\nIn ClipManager::DefineScrollLayers, we don't always create a scroll ID\nfor each ASR. We may fail to get the scroll metadata, or it may not be\nscrollable, in which case we should use the scroll ID of its ancestor\n(or the root scroll ID if there is no ancestor). This should fix a crash\nwhere we simply assumed the leaf of an ASR tree will always have a valid\nscroll ID.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10708", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/ClipManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/ClipManager.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a7b21829921c219dda2aa58a243b5ba2232c588d", "parents": ["d29760cf44dd39a8716e5557329df863d0ccd91c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541603029, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "10129": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502169 - about:studies: wait for more elements before interacting with them in tests. r=Gijs, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10630", "files": ["toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_about_studies.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "74833aee1389ae0174a08831d53b0dc851e06bd7", "parents": ["a7b21829921c219dda2aa58a243b5ba2232c588d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541607730, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10130": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503082 - Clear CanvasShutdownObserver::mCanvas when the canvas goes away. r=nical, a=RyanVM\n\nIt is possible for the CanvasRenderingContext2D to be destroyed while\nwe're in the middle of the call to nsObserverService::NotifyObservers()\nfor shutdown. This leaves the shutdown observer with a dangling pointer\nto the canvas, so this patch explicitly clears the pointer when the\ncontext goes away.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10777", "files": ["dom/canvas/CanvasRenderingContext2D.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "522a5434e0a42890c5292c0228eea366e7dabafd", "parents": ["74833aee1389ae0174a08831d53b0dc851e06bd7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Benjamin Bouvier \u003cbenj@benj.me\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502886 - Delete wasm breakpoints when the wasm instance's Zone is swept. r=jonco, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/gc/Zone.cpp", "js/src/vm/Debugger.cpp", "js/src/vm/Debugger.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmDebug.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmDebug.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmInstance.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f65ddbf6c00545fcf8f56df06ee2a7e3811e5faf", "parents": ["522a5434e0a42890c5292c0228eea366e7dabafd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Benjamin Bouvier \u003cbenj@benj.me\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502886 - Test. r=jonco, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/wasm/regress/bug1502886.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "12500028fe79390ae7d2d4128acf92d2c0d18733", "parents": ["f65ddbf6c00545fcf8f56df06ee2a7e3811e5faf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499861 - Make HTMLOptionsCollection::mSelect into a strong reference. r=qDot, a=RyanVM\n\nThe cycle collector makes weak references like this obsolete.", "files": ["dom/html/HTMLOptionsCollection.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLOptionsCollection.h", "dom/html/HTMLSelectElement.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLSelectElement.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "50bb4e6c8ab511f9103f8ddc8d0044ef49c31318", "parents": ["12500028fe79390ae7d2d4128acf92d2c0d18733"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541621010, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10131": {"changesets": [{"author": "Bumsik Kim \u003ck.bumsik@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1496377 - Fix and add test_mediarecorder_state_transition.html in tests. r=jya a=test-only\n\nThis resolves two problems:\n\n1. test_mediarecorder_state_transition.html was not in mochitest.ini.\n2. The test set in the file has some wrong test cases, especially after D7910.\n\nTo verify the state transition cases is trivial as the state error policy in the W3C spec is very simple:\n\n1. start() can be called only when it is \"inactive\" state.\n2. All other functions, pause(), resume(), stop(), and requestData() must not be called when it's \"inactive\" state. Otherwise it will be okay, regardless of the order and how many they are called.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8190", "files": ["dom/media/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/media/test/test_mediarecorder_state_transition.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "438c1b303119f55a93f537780329f2a03e354ecd", "parents": ["50bb4e6c8ab511f9103f8ddc8d0044ef49c31318"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503855 - Use December as previous month for credit card validity check if it's January r=MattN a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11020", "files": ["toolkit/modules/tests/xpcshell/test_CreditCard.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5f7fd2e8f39f1f24ccf722e3e5bbce7401017e2e", "parents": ["438c1b303119f55a93f537780329f2a03e354ecd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541624510, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "aiakab@mozilla.com"}, "10132": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1492128: [mozrelease] Tweak buglist email to be nicely formated and not use URL shortener; r=mtabara a=release\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11096", "files": ["python/mozrelease/mozrelease/buglist_creator.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5f5ccfe856314f31191c1d15e2636daa89d17b17", "parents": ["5f7fd2e8f39f1f24ccf722e3e5bbce7401017e2e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541650269, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mozilla@hocat.ca"}, "10133": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e 338168e5b1f4\nbg -\u003e d50116224536\nda -\u003e 9498982e25b3\ndsb -\u003e 298ad2e97831\nes-MX -\u003e a4f05534bc82\nff -\u003e 51580bd4f707\nfi -\u003e 2db7e485a6d7\nhsb -\u003e 932b82c67b02\nid -\u003e 3b9ea702e170\nit -\u003e 148578fa4553\nlv -\u003e f5e79da1b020\nms -\u003e d35e7492de6d\nnl -\u003e e8aade26590a\npl -\u003e b87f04ecc26e\nrm -\u003e cb084643be30\nro -\u003e 444e58f466b9", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "56656ee0876562eea97c29d7917b5f588c602d44", "parents": ["5f5ccfe856314f31191c1d15e2636daa89d17b17"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e 338168e5b1f4\nbg -\u003e 59e6872b6861\nbn-BD -\u003e c7c33fa38983\nbr -\u003e 13e3d88b6e6a\nda -\u003e 476347dcae28\ndsb -\u003e 298ad2e97831\nes-MX -\u003e 14eb67b9a661\nff -\u003e 51580bd4f707\nfi -\u003e 5a6b09be9d64\nhr -\u003e 08e42d6fb736\nhsb -\u003e 932b82c