IE -\u003e f3908a1bdbe1\ngd -\u003e fb2f90fb6c55\ngl -\u003e d1f341097504\ngn -\u003e 1b34bd85e970\ngu-IN -\u003e b9e436701735\nhe -\u003e 2089fb701e11\nhi-IN -\u003e e3c5a66c3a31\nhr -\u003e 70f7cc013b43\nhsb -\u003e 779bf1ff93be\nhu -\u003e a7696eac59a0\nhy-AM -\u003e 39402ec448d5\nia -\u003e a014929c8b9f\nid -\u003e 64354ab44f7d\nis -\u003e 58a1e1824c2b\nja -\u003e 992f87605e0b\nja-JP-mac -\u003e 7d0f88bb10a8\nka -\u003e 178d06697a7e\nkab -\u003e ab445bdeb0ab\nkk -\u003e d651702a031d\nkn -\u003e 02226c531652", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7bb875130d4e5c249d11c9c0cfab169071d63159", "parents": ["fb147ae7d462437c5233ca734c572014b6190cfe"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541678424, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10138": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Tung \u003cshes050117@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425146 - P1 - Ensure the schema for the cache.sqlite is up to date beforing accessing it; r=janv a=jcristau\n\nBug 1290481 introduces the padding mechanism, but there was a corner case which\nweren't handled correctly. It created a chance to access cache database before\nacutally checking the database version and schema upgrade. If the schema of\ncache.sqlite is too old and the padding file disappear, it breaks origins\ninitialization. This patch ensure the schema is updated to the newest before\naccessing it.", "files": ["dom/cache/QuotaClient.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b82e4143ecdbf2d35811fc952738c2d7ab772f7f", "parents": ["7bb875130d4e5c249d11c9c0cfab169071d63159"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Tung \u003cshes050117@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425146 - P2 - Add a test reproducing the reported issue to verify that a Cache directory without a padding file and with an old version of the database doesn't break the storage initialization; r=janv a=jcristau\n\nAn issue for missing the \"response_padding_size\" column in cache.sqlite was\nreported in bug 1425146 comment 39. This test reproduces it and is mainly to\nensure that a Cache directory which lacks a directory padding file and contains\nan old version of cache.sqlite can still be initialized successfully.", "files": ["dom/cache/test/xpcshell/bug1425146_profile.zip", "dom/cache/test/xpcshell/test_bug1425146.js", "dom/cache/test/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7a1bcf3d6977e2944c6fd0c80b713e0add581848", "parents": ["b82e4143ecdbf2d35811fc952738c2d7ab772f7f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1493711 - Pref off downloading langpacks outside of release r=jaws a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8909", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/preferences/browserLanguages.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_browser_languages_subdialog.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8034ed187c948ad0cfea0bca8d840f5fa3c3a980", "parents": ["7a1bcf3d6977e2944c6fd0c80b713e0add581848"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Striemer \u003cmstriemer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1493711 - Enable langpack download on release and Beta r=jaws a=jcristau\n\nFix the message bar showing when the \"search\" option is selected. A value\nwas added in 597134aa665 for testing but the change handler was expecting\nno value to be set for search.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10967", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_browser_languages_subdialog.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "24ac9d53d202349388e7d35b5bf1934aa76fdc72", "parents": ["8034ed187c948ad0cfea0bca8d840f5fa3c3a980"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498233 - Stub out getBrowserForOuterWindowID for GeckoViewTab. r=jchen a=jcristau\n\nGeckoViewTab stubs out gBrowser on the root window for WebExtension compatibility.\nLoginManagerParent also looks for gBrowser on windows that are handling username\nand password form fills, and expects it to implement getBrowserForOuterWindowID.\n\nThis patch makes the stub implement getBrowserForOuterWindowID, which just returns\nthe lone GeckoViewTab browser.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10750", "files": ["mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewTab.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "410f4e7ae2feb52dc23db8892829e1b767477849", "parents": ["24ac9d53d202349388e7d35b5bf1934aa76fdc72"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kyle Machulis \u003ckyle@nonpolynomial.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499169 - Split MIME type of nsObjectLoadingContent when retreived from tag; r=bzbarsky a=jcristau\n\nMIME type should be trimmed of parameters whenever it is retreived\nfrom the tag it relates to, otherwise other checks may fail.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10803", "files": ["dom/base/nsObjectLoadingContent.cpp", "dom/base/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/base/test/test_bug1499169.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd20a71aba8a9f29804c3a848cd12c75750626a7", "parents": ["410f4e7ae2feb52dc23db8892829e1b767477849"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Petru Lingurar \u003cpetru.lingurar@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499415 - Check mExtensionPermissionsHelper for null before using it; r=sdaswani a=jcristau\n\n`mExtensionPermissionsHelper` is initialized in BrowserApp's onCreate() and\nnullified in it's onDestroy().\nGeckoApp's onCreate() can finish after BrowserApp's onDestroy() because it uses\nbackground initialization.\n`mExtensionPermissionsHelper` will be checked for null before using it and\nif null it's safe to ignore it's method's results as it only can be null if the\napp was already closed.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10910", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e578f064314f15077162d153fa1f7c1f84309e37", "parents": ["cd20a71aba8a9f29804c3a848cd12c75750626a7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503572 - Enable SSL_CERT_VERIFICATION_ERRORS histogram on release. r=janerik a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10875", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/histogram-whitelists.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aaa628592fed21ccbad82fd5368268b58d41f2c3", "parents": ["e578f064314f15077162d153fa1f7c1f84309e37"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505024 - Disable codeMirror search addon in JsTerm; r=Honza a=jcristau\n\nThis patches fixes a bug where hitting Cmd+F while\nthe filter input of the console was focused was\ntriggering codeMirror search addon, displaying the\nsearch UI *in* JsTerm.\nTo prevent this, we add the ability for any consumer\nof the Editor component to disable the search addon.\nIn the editor, in such case, we simply don't initialize\nthe event listeners that activate the search addon.\nA test case is added to ensure we don't regress this.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11037", "files": ["devtools/client/sourceeditor/editor.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/components/JSTerm.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser_webconsole_keyboard_accessibility.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f73495a359977fab71404c1046c5a832d8286ce4", "parents": ["aaa628592fed21ccbad82fd5368268b58d41f2c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505520 - Back out bug 1478455. r=xidorn a=jcristau\n\nIt breaks websites.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11232", "files": ["layout/style/res/html.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c329b2c093c0ff455a89a5909d577d5f389b20f4", "parents": ["f73495a359977fab71404c1046c5a832d8286ce4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1541680021, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ebalazs@mozilla.com"}, "10139": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nkn -\u003e 02226c531652\nko -\u003e 4aa22ca169b8\nlij -\u003e e55b3ded4460\nlo -\u003e 8d1a4294c1d7\nlt -\u003e 6838fe4542b4\nlv -\u003e 6cee7fe558a7\nmai -\u003e af28f5c53017\nml -\u003e 8cf583fee496\nmr -\u003e ed7077a6a7f8\nms -\u003e a3852e1ee380\nmy -\u003e b7099d8e418f\nnb-NO -\u003e 90e289da7260\nne-NP -\u003e deb682b11d16\nnn-NO -\u003e 8b8d71dfa59b\noc -\u003e 5db1a9dd95cf\nor -\u003e cc9caa5ed714\npa-IN -\u003e 016bbb6787ac\npt-BR -\u003e a9bee361ef48\npt-PT -\u003e 9ccbf99ccff9\nrm -\u003e 20a753d3f66b\nro -\u003e 4a9e84a82c8a\nru -\u003e e8d3e4756671\nsk -\u003e 2ebd749fce0c\nsl -\u003e 35ab0a36edbf\nson -\u003e 8e12efa4491d\nsq -\u003e 3fbdde6014ed\nsr -\u003e d4b8c141600e\nsv-SE -\u003e ad16f5016901\nta -\u003e 7110b894b8b6\nte -\u003e 1fc79323f535\nth -\u003e bdb28bf54bb8\ntr -\u003e 8ec3325e14e7\ntrs -\u003e bc35da09dff1\nuk -\u003e ea527a8f9708\nur -\u003e 4ab9205b7a1a\nuz -\u003e 87bb8d3dcf69\nvi -\u003e aacfc9d519ab\nwo -\u003e e60dd6bd7d87\nxh -\u003e b8a1bfb07c6a\nzam -\u003e 0aa29e6d85ac", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ecf5c18a85ca4388931b86294d0a9dc4dda3