, "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset ec9a256c6703 (bug 1505514) for failing gradle toolchains a=backout", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/build.gradle"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4fe80a60a6a04458add149d68b2dd2f7224f65f9", "parents": ["bc53b14823111dc83c79092fba260fa0b436da78"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499193 - Add new SEARCH_COUNTS telemetry for internal search engine alias usage. r=mkaply a=jcristau\n\nModify `BrowserUsageTelemetry.recordSearch` to take an alias instead of the bool `isAlias`. If an alias is given and it's an internal alias of the given engine, then increment a new `\"engineName.@engine.source\"` key under the `SEARCH_COUNTS` histogram -- in addition to incrementing the usual `\"engineName.source\"` key under that same histogram.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10633\n* * *\nBug 1499193 - Follow-up: Update metadata for the SEARCH_COUNTS keyed histogram. r=mkaply\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11382", "files": ["browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml", "browser/modules/BrowserUsageTelemetry.jsm", "browser/modules/test/browser/browser_UsageTelemetry_urlbar.js", "browser/modules/test/browser/head.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/histogram-whitelists.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7221b7dad3fac285b301f3b43275c76854f79a7", "parents": ["4fe80a60a6a04458add149d68b2dd2f7224f65f9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504370 - Update SEARCH_COUNTS telemetry for private browsing mode r=mkaply a=jcristau\n\n* If a search is performed in a private window and the new pref `browser.engagement.search_counts.pbm` is true, then do not record `SEARCH_COUNTS` telemetry. Note that the the pref must be true. If it's false or doesn't exist, then we record telemetry even in pbm like we normally do currently. (We record `SEARCH_COUNTS` telemetry in two places: (1) In BrowserUsageTelemetry.jsm, and (2) \"in-content\" telemetry directly in the search service. So skip both of those places.)\n* Also skip the other ancillary telemetry recorded by `BrowserUsageTelemetry._recordSearch`: a keyed scalar and a telemetry event.\n* I made some modifications to the search service to let me test the \"in-content\" telemetry keys\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10851", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/components/extensions/parent/ext-search.js", "browser/modules/BrowserUsageTelemetry.jsm", "browser/modules/test/browser/browser_UsageTelemetry_urlbar.js", "toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a106808198a6b0eac935d7bf9cecc3fb9d5a975a", "parents": ["f7221b7dad3fac285b301f3b43275c76854f79a7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Karl Tomlinson \u003ckarlt+@karlt.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503950 insert new timeline events after existing events at the same time even when of the same type r=padenot a=jcristau\n\nDepends on D10861\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10862", "files": ["dom/media/webaudio/AudioEventTimeline.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "42b57103a046eea029cf9f8b6d80f694ce84c469", "parents": ["a106808198a6b0eac935d7bf9cecc3fb9d5a975a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Makoto Kato \u003cm_kato@ga2.so-net.ne.jp\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1501804 - browser.display.use_document_fonts is integer, not boolean. r=snorp a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10873", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoRuntimeSettings.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a691b474af0cac5d467179f06a9f07c37a3eba44", "parents": ["42b57103a046eea029cf9f8b6d80f694ce84c469"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Farre \u003cfarre@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1501138 - Make sure that timeout iterator advances. r=peterv a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11327", "files": ["dom/base/TimeoutManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4e6ab55cc0bee5450aca0a8c780657c9acc6e020", "parents": ["a691b474af0cac5d467179f06a9f07c37a3eba44"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Maries \u003crmaries@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504165 - Two Sponsored cards are wrongly displayed after increasing the number of Pocket recommendations r=k88hudson a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/common/Reducers.jsm", "browser/components/newtab/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js", "browser/components/newtab/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js.map", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/common/Reducers.test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a4175191b29b274d59ed117567ec03df9d6b8cf5", "parents": ["4e6ab55cc0bee5450aca0a8c780657c9acc6e020"], "tags": []}], "date": 1542036157, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rmaries@mozilla.com"}, "10167": {"changesets": [{"author": "Razvan Maries \u003crmaries@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset a691b474af0c (bug 1501804) for failing Android at org.mozilla.geckoview.test.crash.CrashTest.crashParent a=backout", "files": ["mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/geckoview/GeckoRuntimeSettings.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d74a918ff930da31a1ef3ad019ae27fdc75b0d44", "parents": ["a4175191b29b274d59ed117567ec03df9d6b8cf5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1542039863, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "rmaries@mozilla.com"}, "10168": {"changesets": [{"author": "Razvan Maries \u003crmaries@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 2 changesets (bug 149919