ase a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nfr -\u003e 58e63dc32fe2\npt-PT -\u003e 5c6339a9405c\ntr -\u003e 26ce77bb975b", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6893da860f67da291b5be307556d016b4d729edd", "parents": ["0555620572c241eae8903ea77afe4859c5d25b10"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nfr -\u003e 58e63dc32fe2\nia -\u003e 728b7d43b8e7\nkm -\u003e 38760f72b598\npt-PT -\u003e 5c6339a9405c\ntr -\u003e 26ce77bb975b", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "076cf9eb016ed988b27b20e9073970ea217a3ae5", "parents": ["6893da860f67da291b5be307556d016b4d729edd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1542214828, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10194": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1506920 - [taskgraph] Track parent images in docker image digests. r=dustin, a=release\n\nThe digest for a docker image task did not include the digest for the parent\nimage in it, and so in particular did not depend on the versions of packages\nincluded in a parent image.\n\nIf two branches have a docker image with identical docker files, but different\nparents, this would lead to them both getting the same digest, leading to\nunexpected interference between the branches.\n\nThis fixes things by including the digest of the parent image as input into the\ndigest of child images.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11807", "files": ["taskcluster/docs/attributes.rst", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/docker_image.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/cached_tasks.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e23852ca141b9cafe85d5ae758d06845d7b22d0b", "parents": ["076cf9eb016ed988b27b20e9073970ea217a3ae5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1332064 - [marionette] Re-enable test_navigation.py:test_focus_after_navigation. r=jgraham, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11755", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_navigation.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d525167ebef78d9c2ef8a863618d9410159ecfd4", "parents": ["e23852ca141b9cafe85d5ae758d06845d7b22d0b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503536 - Call ApplySettings in MediaEngineWebRTCMicrophoneSource::Start. r=pehrsons, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D10347", "files": ["dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineWebRTCAudio.cpp", "dom/media/webrtc/MediaEngineWebRTCAudio.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "929f848d3a54977c8b6ea468fff80954cafa6bf0", "parents": ["d525167ebef78d9c2ef8a863618d9410159ecfd4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504274 - Close Tabs to the Right in a multiselect context should close all tabs to the right of the contextual tab that are not selected. r=dao, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11250", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js", "browser/base/content/test/tabs/browser_multiselect_tabs_close_tabs_to_the_right.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9bddcf6d4659e0c6b764de1dc6fdcc7727db3e0", "parents": ["929f848d3a54977c8b6ea468fff80954cafa6bf0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miko Mynttinen \u003cmikokm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504592 - Mark the right frame modified when caret changes. r=tnikkel, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11316", "files": ["layout/base/nsCaret.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c6949142e640b8d3727055053ee471b3eeb7d2e6", "parents": ["b9bddcf6d4659e0c6b764de1dc6fdcc7727db3e0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504691 - Read certs from local and roaming on Windows. r=Felipe, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11360", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "23d0264564e5dd6a1ed4f9cce45188f7c60d28c2", "parents": ["c6949142e640b8d3727055053ee471b3eeb7d2e6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505817 - Handle the case where a float is dynamically inserted inside a continuation. r=dbaron, a=jcristau\n\nThe first assertion that fails here, and which causes all the havoc later, is:\n\n  https://dev.searchfox.org/mozilla-central/rev/6e0e603f4852b8e571e5b8ae133e772b18b6016e/layout/generic/BlockReflowInput.cpp#578\n\nThat happens because the float has been dynamically inserted directly under one\nof the continuations of the column set, not under the first. So that assertion\ndoesn't really hold.\n\nProperly steal the float if that happens.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11359", "files": ["layout/generic/BlockReflowInput.cpp", "layout/generic/crashtests/1505817.html", "layout/generic/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5b355cd76cea5b71bd2affd16bcf6f258a5125eb", "parents": ["23d0264564e5dd6a1ed4f9cce45188f7c60d28c2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1542216251, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10195": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dylan Roeh \u003cdroeh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503724 - Fix progress bar on first load in Fennec custom tabs. r=esawin, a=jcristau\n\nThere's a race condition here where we receive STATE_START before we've enabled GeckoViewProgressChild; this patch starts listening for web progress in onInit() rather than onEnable() so that we can guarantee progress tracking will work whenever a ProgressDelegate is set.", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/geckoview/GeckoViewProgressContent.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ab056dc26a8334daba227f5c9b2bb67f99e51c1", "parents": ["5b355cd76cea5b71bd2affd16bcf6f258a5125eb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Abdoulaye O. Ly \u003cablayelyfondou@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1500098 - Reopen multi-selected tabs in container. r=Gijs, a=jcristau\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11145", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js", "browser/base/content/test/tabs/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/tabs/browser_multiselect_tabs_reopen_in_container.js", "browser/base/content/test/tabs/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5505a22a57d05c620a3fb81eb16f220454708b5f", "parents": ["0ab056dc26a8334daba227f5c9b2bb67f99e51c1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eugen Sawin \u003cesawin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503560 - [1.2] Override tracking protection pref on GeckoView to re-enable blocklist updates. r=francois, a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/components/url-classifier/SafeBrowsing.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e14b94e8cc97a78bf833f809d2f668db6d615c43", "parents": ["5505a22a57d05c620a3fb81eb16f220454708b5f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504854 - Autofilled search shortcuts should show a single \"Search with Engine\" heuristic result in the popup. r=mak, a=jcristau\n\nAll we need to do is set `_searchEngineAliasMatch` with an empty query so that we don't try to add any more results. That hits the existing case where the user types out a full @ alias and we show only the \"search with engine\" heuristic result.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11547", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/UnifiedComplete.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/test_autofill_search_engine_aliases.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d719e13dbb8b9f9729d5c8bbd00157a43452721b", "parents": ["e14b94e8cc97a78bf833f809d2f668db6d615c43"], "tags": []}], "date": 1542223342, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10196": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 0825a68344ef\ncs -\u003e b7411d62090c\nes-MX -\u003e 9b63b73c88bc\nhr -\u003e 8dcb35965485\nka -\u003e 8f1a93caba7f\nsv-SE -\u003e 2e40305c7186", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "da77ae6bcf6403ceb94574399fe23a13aa8decbc", "parents": ["d719e13dbb8b9f9729d5c8bbd00157a43452721b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbe -\u003e 0825a68344ef\ncs -\u003e b7411d62090c\nes-MX -\u003e 9b63b73c88bc\nhr -\u003e 8dcb35965485\nka -\u003e 847317aad36a\nsv-SE -\u003e 2e40305c7186", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7585190c59546c832cc474d19970ddb2a186df01", "parents": ["da77ae6bcf6403ceb94574399fe23a13aa8decbc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1542229225, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10197": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1507035 - Fix run sizes for size classes \u003e= 16KB on systems with large pages. r=njn, a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11836", "files": ["memory/build/mozjemalloc.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "567929ba659f6488b3c9feeb5d2f6ec1f4ed13ba", "parents": ["7585190c59546c832cc474d19970ddb2a186df01"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Cooper \u003cmcooper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1502410 - Don't use deleteBranch in Normandy. r=Gijs,adw, a=ritu\n\nnsIPrefBranch.deleteBranch doesn't work as documented when the preference's\ndefault value was set very early after Firefox has started, such as when\nNormandy sets startup branches. This is filed as bug 1505941. In order to work\naround this problem, this patch makes Normandy never use deleteBranch, except\nin tests where it is safe to do so.\n\nWith this patch, an experiment that is run on the default branch for a\npreference that does not have a default value in the tree cannot be promptly\nunenrolled, instead we must wait until the preference is naturally cleared when\nFirefox restarts. This is better than never unenrolling though.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D11383", "files": ["browser/components/tests/browser/browser_urlbar_matchBuckets_migration60.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/lib/PrefUtils.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/lib/PreferenceExperiments.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/lib/PreferenceRollouts.jsm", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_PreferenceExperiments.js", "toolkit/components/normandy/test/browser/browser_actions_PreferenceRolloutAction.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "331cafa0d8476c853ee44ba53353383cbbd8656f", "parents": ["567929ba659f6488b3c9feeb5d2f6ec1f4ed13ba"], "tags": []}], "date": 1542231123, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10198": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nit -\u003e 76791cd1f033", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git