ion: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8584", "files": ["dom/base/nsDocument.cpp", "toolkit/components/antitracking/test/browser/storageAccessAPIHelpers.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7b24c0c835bf54698cf49b5a21538bddd616642b", "parents": ["8efab497c2e6f710481d215e360650b220865269"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498720 - Ensure that we revoke a subframe's storage access when it is removed from the DOM r=baku\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8615", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bb057b527690f626ad617828044c96cd113d4122", "parents": ["7b24c0c835bf54698cf49b5a21538bddd616642b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan-Erik Rediger \u003cjrediger@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1481812 - Refactor memory gathering into its own module r=chutten\n\nThis avoids loading the remaining parts of TelemetrySession in a content process.\nThis saves around 10 kb of memory.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8378", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/performance/browser_startup_content.js", "toolkit/components/telemetry/app/TelemetryController.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/moz.build", "toolkit/components/telemetry/other/MemoryTelemetry.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/pings/TelemetrySession.jsm", "toolkit/components/telemetry/tests/unit/test_TelemetrySession.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "801c33dcde58caa5a8be251eb1b0f9597cd26777", "parents": ["bb057b527690f626ad617828044c96cd113d4122"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ursula Sarracini \u003cursulasarracini@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498378 - Actually remove the old onboarding add-on's prefs r=Gijs\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8598", "files": ["browser/components/nsBrowserGlue.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f1a8f5f2079797d054575d5b8877a5e4654b7650", "parents": ["801c33dcde58caa5a8be251eb1b0f9597cd26777"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1491455 - Update the security and content blocking icons in the control centre r=johannh\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8638", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/controlcenter/connection.svg", "browser/themes/shared/controlcenter/tracking-protection.svg"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc9eacb1243742cb91903442938e0664d5a8817e", "parents": ["f1a8f5f2079797d054575d5b8877a5e4654b7650"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484989 - Prevent JsTerm to steal focus when reloading a page; r=bgrins.\n\nJsTerm's focus function was called in clearOutput, which\nwe call when navigating to a new page (if Persist Logs is\nnot checked).\nThis means that we were forcing the JsTerm to be focused\neach time the user navigated while having the console open.\nThis behavior, can be annoying, or at worst, if you're\ndebugging a focus issue in your content page, completely maddening.\nThe fix is striaghtforward: do not call focus in clearOutput.\nA test is added to make sure we don't regress this.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8701", "files": ["devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser.ini", "devtools/client/webconsole/test/mochitest/browser_jsterm_focus_reload.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/webconsole-frame.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "57c85fc5a5bc6a1c25fc0050aa4350bbe82f6ecf", "parents": ["fc9eacb1243742cb91903442938e0664d5a8817e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas Chevobbe \u003cnchevobbe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425542 - Move inspectObjectActor away from jsterm; r=bgrins.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8519", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/toolbox.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/components/JSTerm.js", "devtools/client/webconsole/webconsole-frame.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "71a04ddae0fad8b796e63f482269e825b98fd686", "parents": ["57c85fc5a5bc6a1c25fc0050aa4350bbe82f6ecf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1475989 - add support for loadPath blocking r=mikedeboer\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D7620", "files": ["toolkit/components/search/nsSearchService.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/data/search_blacklist.json", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/data/search_ignorelist.json", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_blacklist.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_ignorelist.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_json_cache_blacklist.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/test_json_cache_ignorelist.js", "toolkit/components/search/tests/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ba17ddb6432e1c67c860994697a565f9a663ecec", "parents": ["71a04ddae0fad8b796e63f482269e825b98fd686"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1425365: geckodriver: re-enable rust tests on windows; r=whimboo\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8723", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "04459ddd517a051f4dd0c69c6177de1a61921bc9", "parents": ["ba17ddb6432e1c67c860994697a565f9a663ecec"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Graham \u003cjames@hoppipolla.co.uk\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1499061 - Only do wpt mozdevice imports when running fennec, r=gbrown\n\nOtherwise some users see problems due to missing psutil.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8715", "files": ["testing/web-platform/mach_commands.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b9dcee0058edfd5020f141285e021cc912c27d4", "parents": ["04459ddd517a051f4dd0c69c6177de1a61921bc9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498699 - Move the LAYERS_UPDATED notification from AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator to UiCompositorControllerParent. r=jnicol\n\nThis extracts code that is conceptually unrelated to the dynamic toolbar\nfrom the dynamic toolbar codebase. It is a stepping stone to being able\nto not instantiate the AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator at all for\nnon-Fennec android products.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8657", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator.h", "gfx/layers/composite/AsyncCompositionManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/UiCompositorControllerParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/UiCompositorControllerParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dcd095eb89108d1171c25b9d32ca01a6d317087f", "parents": ["9b9dcee0058edfd5020f141285e021cc912c27d4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498699 - Move the FIRST_PAINT notification from AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator to UiCompositorControllerParent. r=jnicol\n\nDepends on D8657\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D8658", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AndroidDynamicToolbarAnimator.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/AsyncCompositionManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/UiCompositorControllerParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/UiCompositorControllerParent.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "da505775320b6d209ecac91e25d018b7b7197894", "parents": ["dcd095eb89108d1171c25b9d32ca01a6d317087f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "des